The app is a basic todolist app. The user can create new todos, archive 
them,delete them, email them, mark them as done or undone. It also provides 
stats on your items.

Sweet citations! They're in the code but heres a summary!

The itemlistmanager and itemlist controller names were inspired by Abram Hindle's studentpicker names.

The itemlongclick method from mainactivity and archiveactivity was adapted from 
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8846707/how-to-implement-a-long-click-listener-on-a-listview
by Dinesh Sharma

The dialog and any other dialog buttons were adapted from
http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/dialogs.html

The actionbars and other action bars were adapted from
Code taken and modified from https://developer.android.com/training/basics/actionbar/adding-buttons.html

Setting up the intents to send to an email app from the emailactivity was adapted from
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2197741/how-can-i-send-emails-from-my-android-application
by fiXedd

The saving and loading from a file. The template and methods was used from
http://developer.android.com/training/basics/data-storage/files.html

